newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 929 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 929 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totaled 929 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 76 wheat contracts, 342 corn, 466 soybean, 17 soymeal, and 28 soyoil futures contracts traded, along with 4 wheat call and 3 soybean call options.

The overnight trend for corn was 3/4 to two cents per bushel higher, soybeans 5-3/4 to 5-1/2 cents higher, wheat 1/4 to 1-1/2 cents higher, soymeal 90 cents per ton higher, and soyoil 0.02 higher to 0.07 cent per lb lower.
